<i>Or a shrine on a hill.</i>

535
00:30:01,366 --> 00:30:02,367
Can I pay with e-money?

536
00:30:02,433 --> 00:30:04,369
Sorry, we only take cash.

537
00:30:04,435 --> 00:30:05,270
What?

538
00:30:14,879 --> 00:30:16,514
What's your first choice university?

539
00:30:17,248 --> 00:30:18,716
Aoyama, I think.

540
00:30:22,153 --> 00:30:27,225
MAY I GET INTO AOYAMA UNIVERSITY

541
00:30:30,061 --> 00:30:31,129
Something feels off.

542
00:30:32,397 --> 00:30:33,898
I think you're missing "Gakuin."

543
00:30:35,567 --> 00:30:36,701
Right.

544
00:30:40,805 --> 00:30:43,541
AOYAMA GAKUIN UNIVERSITY

545
00:30:44,042 --> 00:30:44,876
<i>What about Rome?</i>

546
00:30:45,443 --> 00:30:47,412
During the press conference,

547
00:30:47,478 --> 00:30:50,415
when the princess is asked
which city she enjoyed the most,

548
00:30:50,481 --> 00:30:54,118
Audrey Hepburn looks at Gregory Peck

549
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:57,088
and says, "Rome."

550
00:30:59,357 --> 00:31:00,391
What?

551
00:31:00,458 --> 00:31:02,427
Have you never seen <i>Roman Holiday</i>?

552
00:31:02,493 --> 00:31:03,328
Nope.

553
00:31:03,394 --> 00:31:04,395
These few years,

554
00:31:04,462 --> 00:31:06,497
it's just been <i>Tora-san</i>
and <i>Truck Yaro</i> films for me.

555
00:31:06,564 --> 00:31:07,565
Truck…

556
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:10,435
That's no help at all!

557
00:31:11,169 --> 00:31:14,305
Let's just go with Rome, then.
Hamura, can't we film in Italy?

558
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:15,240
No.

559
00:31:16,774 --> 00:31:18,710
I'm no expert,

560
00:31:19,244 --> 00:31:22,714
but if all this brainstorming
isn't leading anywhere,

561
00:31:22,780 --> 00:31:26,618
maybe you should finish the first episode
in a way that satisfies you.

562
00:31:26,684 --> 00:31:28,119
I agree.

563
00:31:29,787 --> 00:31:32,957
I'm not writing for folks
who'll just watch one episode and bail.

564
00:31:33,691 --> 00:31:36,294
This is Kentaro Emo's
final work before retirement.

565
00:31:36,361 --> 00:31:38,263
It needs a flawless four-part structure.

566
00:31:38,329 --> 00:31:41,633
Every foreshadowing in all the episodes
must be resolved in the finale.

567
00:31:41,699 --> 00:31:45,703
And the final piece falls into place
in the last scene just before "The End."

568
00:31:45,770 --> 00:31:46,804
It's the only way.

569
00:31:48,006 --> 00:31:49,374
Do they have to be resolved?

570
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,375
They do.

571
00:31:50,942 --> 00:31:52,277
I'm a perfectionist.

572
00:31:52,343 --> 00:31:54,012
It's always been my approach.

573
00:31:54,078 --> 00:31:56,648
When you have a goal,
the path becomes clear.

574
00:31:56,714 --> 00:31:59,450
Then, writing the rest becomes easy.

575
00:32:01,886 --> 00:32:03,087
Do you think you're a god?

576
00:32:04,322 --> 00:32:06,424
When it comes to my dramas, yes.

577
00:32:07,125 --> 00:32:09,227
I have the perspective of a god.

578
00:32:09,294 --> 00:32:11,162
No offense, but I think that's arrogant.

579
00:32:12,563 --> 00:32:13,831
You don't know what happens

580
00:32:14,399 --> 00:32:17,302
or how long something will last.
That's what makes it intriguing.

581
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:20,838
You can't write
unless you know the finale?

582
00:32:20,905 --> 00:32:21,973
Give me a break!

583
00:32:22,740 --> 00:32:23,741
The…

584
00:32:24,375 --> 00:32:25,944
The finale for Junko and me

585
00:32:27,312 --> 00:32:28,313
is already set!

586
00:32:39,857 --> 00:32:40,692
I win!

587
00:32:40,758 --> 00:32:42,460
Not fair!

588
00:32:44,729 --> 00:32:45,697
Wait!

589
00:32:47,532 --> 00:32:48,466
<i>Sorry.</i>

590
00:32:48,533 --> 00:32:50,134
I didn't mean to yell like that.

591
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:53,771
But…

592
00:32:55,273 --> 00:32:56,507
